A.7 Proof of Theorem 4.2 (Martingale Observer Safety)

Theorem 4.2 (Martingale Observer Safety).
Under the ISS condition, the process M_k = V(k) - \sum_{i=0}^{k-1} (\alpha V(i) + \sigma(\bar{d})) is a supermartingale. The probability that V(k) exceeds a threshold T within N steps is bounded by \exp\left(-\frac{(T - \alpha^k V(0) - \frac{\sigma(\bar{d})}{1-\alpha})^2}{2N\sigma_{\max}^2}\right), where \sigma_{\max} is an upper bound on the one‑step noise.

